                        <interp inst="t18381217-name-194" type="given" value="WILLIAM THOMAS"></interp>WILLIAM THOMAS COOPER</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a warehouseman, in Aldermanbury. The prisoner was in my service in July and October last—he had been my counting-house clerk two years and a half—it was his duty to receive the town accounts for me, and hand them over to me immediately, and then I should enter them in the cash-book—he did not account to me on the 14th of July for 6<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. 10<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. from Cox and Co., nor for either of the sums that have been named.</p>
